
[1]syzygy

   SYZ'YGY, n. [Gr. to join.] The conjunction or opposition of a planet
   with the sun, or of any two of the heavenly bodies. On the phenomena
   and circumstances of the syzygies, depends a great part of the lunar
   theory.
